# Test Rules

## Stack

Vitest + React Testing Library + jsdom. Do not use Jest or Enzyme.

## Traceability — first line

Every test file must start with `// @req SCD-XXX-NNN` citing the requirement under test.

```ts
// @req SCD-FLT-001
import { filterRequirements } from '@/lib/coverage';

describe('filterRequirements', () => {
  it('returns only FR requirements when type filter is FR', () => { ... });
});
```

## Test behavior, not implementation

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — tests observable output
expect(screen.getByRole('cell', { name: 'SCD-API-001' })).toBeInTheDocument();

// ❌ BAD — tests internal state
expect(component.state.filter).toEqual({ type: 'FR' });
```

## Coverage of edge cases

Each data-layer test file must cover: valid input, malformed input, empty list, orphan detection.
Each component test must cover: renders correctly, filters/sorts correctly, empty state.

## No `any` in tests

```ts
// ❌ BAD
const result = parseStats(data as any);

// ✅ GOOD
const result = parseStats(data as unknown as Stats);
```
